				\begin{document}$$\:\mu\:m$$\end{document} to 1000 \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:\mu\:m$$\end{document} for bone tissue regeneration, with smaller pores promoting faster tissue growth and larger pores supporting nutrient transport14–16. Moreover, A high surface area is advantageous for cell attachment. Thus, pore size and surface area are crucial factors in determining the functionality of the scaffold.

